cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper proposes a scheme for training a computerized agent to perform complex human tasks using deep convolutional networks. The paper focuses on the application of the scheme to autonomous highway steering, which falls under the category of robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also heavily relies on deep learning techniques, specifically deep convolutional networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of human supervision, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
